The paper deals with physical layer authentication schemes for wireless networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of information theory to analyze the security of the proposed scheme, which suggests that it could also be classified under information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper proposes a practical framework for incorporating the physical layer authentication mechanism into the current 3GPP Authentication and Key Agreement (AKA) protocol, which involves network infrastructure and system design, indicating that it could also be classified under network and internet architecture (cs.NI) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper mentions the use of Orthogonal Frequency-Division Multiplexing (OFDM) transmission, which is a technique used in multimedia systems (cs.MM).
